attributes.Long form description: The instructor asked the student to mount the Joy Con controllers onto the Nintendo Switch. First the student grabbed the comfort grip and placed it back. Then the student mounted the Joy Con controllers onto the Nintendo Switch. The student had trouble with the blue Joy Con controller, and had to rotate the Nintendo Switch and the controller several times to get them aligned properly. The student accidently turned on the Nintendo Switch. The instructor asked the student to turn off the Nintendo Switch, the student turned off the Nintendo Switch after several attempts. Next the student removed the Joy Con controllers from the Nintendo Switch. The instructor provided directions on how to attach the Joy Con straps. The student attached the straps to the Joy Con controllers. The student had some troubles with attaching the straps. Next the student attached the Joy Con controllers to the comfort grip after removing them Joy Con controllers from the straps. The student then stands up the Nintendo Switch using the kickstand on the back. The student then turns on the Nintendo Switch. The instructor requests the student to turn off the Nintendo Switch. The student then exchanges the game card in the Nintendo Switch with the one on the table. The student then is instructed to remove the SD card. The instructor directs the student to where they can find the SD card behind the kickstand. The student then swaps the SD card with the SD card that was on the table. The student then turned the Nintendo Switch on and then off.
